ee years old.</span></li><li class=\"\" htag=\"li\"><span class=\"unx\">I've forgotten most of what I learned at school.</span></li><li class=\"\" htag=\"li\"><span class=\"unx\">It's a bit overwhelming at first but don't worry, you'll soon learn.</span></li><li class=\"\" htag=\"li\"><span class=\"unx\">Most of the kids here are eager to learn.</span></li><li class=\"\" htag=\"li\"><span class=\"unx\">She's very interested in learning more about Japanese culture.</span></li><li class=\"\" htag=\"li\"><span class=\"unx\">I've got a lot to learn, haven't I?</span></li><li class=\"\" htag=\"li\"><span class=\"unx\">You still have a lot to learn.</span></li></ul></span></div><span class=\"topic-g\"><span class=\"prefix\">Topics </span><a class=\"Ref\" href=\"https://www.oxfordlearnersdictionaries.com/topic/education?level=a1\" title=\"Topic education\"><span class=\"topic\" href=\"l2:people:education?cefr=a1\"><span class=\"topic_name\">Education</span><span class=\"topic_cefr\">a1</span></span></a></span><div class=\"collapse\" htag=\"div\" hclass=\"collapse\"><span class=\"unbox\" id=\"learn_unbox_5\" unbox=\"snippet\"><span class=\"box_title\">Oxford Collocations Dictionary</span><span class=\"body\"><span class=\"unbox\">adverb</span><ul class=\"collocs_list\"><li class=\"li\">a lot</li><li class=\"li\">quickly</li><li class=\"li\">soon</li><li class=\"li\">…</li></ul><span class=\"unbox\">verb + learn</span><ul class=\"collocs_list\"><li class=\"li\">need to</li><li class=\"li\">be eager to</li><li class=\"li\">want to</li><li class=\"li\">…</li></ul><span class=\"unbox\">preposition</span><ul class=\"collocs_list\"><li class=\"li\">about</li><li class=\"li\">from</li><li class=\"li\">through</li><li class=\"li\">…</li></ul><span class=\"xref_to_full_entry\">See <a class=\"Ref\" href=\"https://www.oxfordlearnersdictionaries.com/definition/collocations/learn\" title=\" definition in Collocations\n \">full entry</a></span></span></span></div>          \n</li><li cla